[
    {
        "index": 1,
        "start_time": 7057,
        "end_time": 10427,
        "text": "Perfumers can learn to distinguish\nindividual odors"
    },
    {
        "index": 2,
        "start_time": 10427,
        "end_time": 13946,
        "text": "in a fragrance made of hundreds of scents."
    },
    {
        "index": 3,
        "start_time": 13946,
        "end_time": 16026,
        "text": "Tea experts have been known to sniff out"
    },
    {
        "index": 4,
        "start_time": 16026,
        "end_time": 18467,
        "text": "not just the location \nwhere a tea was from,"
    },
    {
        "index": 5,
        "start_time": 18467,
        "end_time": 22835,
        "text": "but the season of harvest\nand whether it was planted by a plum tree."
    },
    {
        "index": 6,
        "start_time": 22835,
        "end_time": 24728,
        "text": "And the New York City Transit Authority"
    },
    {
        "index": 7,
        "start_time": 24728,
        "end_time": 28717,
        "text": "once had an employee responsible\nonly for sniffing out gas leaks"
    },
    {
        "index": 8,
        "start_time": 28717,
        "end_time": 30738,
        "text": "in the subway system."
    },
    {
        "index": 9,
        "start_time": 30738,
        "end_time": 35248,
        "text": "Can just anyone learn to smell\nwith the sensitivity of those experts?"
    },
    {
        "index": 10,
        "start_time": 35248,
        "end_time": 38728,
        "text": "For most of us, what we smell\nis largely involuntary,"
    },
    {
        "index": 11,
        "start_time": 38728,
        "end_time": 40738,
        "text": "whether it&#39;s garbage behind a restaurant,"
    },
    {
        "index": 12,
        "start_time": 40738,
        "end_time": 43518,
        "text": "the shampoo of the woman leaving\nan elevator as you enter,"
    },
    {
        "index": 13,
        "start_time": 43518,
        "end_time": 46469,
        "text": "or a bakery&#39;s fresh-made bread."
    },
    {
        "index": 14,
        "start_time": 46469,
        "end_time": 49990,
        "text": "With a few million olfactory receptors\nin our noses,"
    },
    {
        "index": 15,
        "start_time": 49990,
        "end_time": 52478,
        "text": "we clearly don&#39;t lack the ability\nto smell well."
    },
    {
        "index": 16,
        "start_time": 52478,
        "end_time": 56139,
        "text": "We just might not always pay close\nenough attention."
    },
    {
        "index": 17,
        "start_time": 56139,
        "end_time": 59068,
        "text": "That&#39;s a shame because we may be\nmissing opportunities"
    },
    {
        "index": 18,
        "start_time": 59068,
        "end_time": 61698,
        "text": "to make strong emotional connections."
    },
    {
        "index": 19,
        "start_time": 61698,
        "end_time": 64300,
        "text": "Smells are powerfully linked to emotions"
    },
    {
        "index": 20,
        "start_time": 64300,
        "end_time": 67161,
        "text": "and can awaken memories of places\nwe&#39;ve long ago left"
    },
    {
        "index": 21,
        "start_time": 67161,
        "end_time": 69109,
        "text": "and people we&#39;ve loved."
    },
    {
        "index": 22,
        "start_time": 69109,
        "end_time": 73469,
        "text": "But fortunately, it is possible\nto train our brains to smell better."
    },
    {
        "index": 23,
        "start_time": 73469,
        "end_time": 77010,
        "text": "For example, Helen Keller was able\nto recognize a person&#39;s work,"
    },
    {
        "index": 24,
        "start_time": 77010,
        "end_time": 78797,
        "text": "and in her words,"
    },
    {
        "index": 25,
        "start_time": 78797,
        "end_time": 81559,
        "text": "distinguish the carpenter\nfrom the iron worker,"
    },
    {
        "index": 26,
        "start_time": 81559,
        "end_time": 84360,
        "text": "the artist from the mason or the chemist,"
    },
    {
        "index": 27,
        "start_time": 84360,
        "end_time": 86770,
        "text": "by a simple inhale."
    },
    {
        "index": 28,
        "start_time": 86770,
        "end_time": 91571,
        "text": "Follow these steps and you too can\nchange the way the world smells to you."
    },
    {
        "index": 29,
        "start_time": 91571,
        "end_time": 94630,
        "text": "First, stick your nose in it."
    },
    {
        "index": 30,
        "start_time": 94630,
        "end_time": 97122,
        "text": "Some animals that are known\nto be great smellers,"
    },
    {
        "index": 31,
        "start_time": 97122,
        "end_time": 99460,
        "text": "like dogs who can sniff out explosives"
    },
    {
        "index": 32,
        "start_time": 99460,
        "end_time": 101899,
        "text": "and pigs who can \nfind truffles underground,"
    },
    {
        "index": 33,
        "start_time": 101899,
        "end_time": 105890,
        "text": "put their noses right at the place\nthey want to smell."
    },
    {
        "index": 34,
        "start_time": 105890,
        "end_time": 109501,
        "text": "Human noses, meanwhile, are casting\naround in the middle of the air,"
    },
    {
        "index": 35,
        "start_time": 109501,
        "end_time": 112452,
        "text": "giving us an anatomical disadvantage."
    },
    {
        "index": 36,
        "start_time": 112452,
        "end_time": 115846,
        "text": "So bring your nose close to the world\naround you."
    },
    {
        "index": 37,
        "start_time": 115846,
        "end_time": 116711,
        "text": "The ground,"
    },
    {
        "index": 38,
        "start_time": 116711,
        "end_time": 117621,
        "text": "surfaces,"
    },
    {
        "index": 39,
        "start_time": 117621,
        "end_time": 118662,
        "text": "objects,"
    },
    {
        "index": 40,
        "start_time": 118662,
        "end_time": 120203,
        "text": "the food in your hand."
    },
    {
        "index": 41,
        "start_time": 120203,
        "end_time": 121631,
        "text": "Get close to your dog,"
    },
    {
        "index": 42,
        "start_time": 121631,
        "end_time": 122520,
        "text": "your partner,"
    },
    {
        "index": 43,
        "start_time": 122520,
        "end_time": 124392,
        "text": "the book you&#39;re reading."
    },
    {
        "index": 44,
        "start_time": 124392,
        "end_time": 126980,
        "text": "Not only will your nose be closer\nto the odor source,"
    },
    {
        "index": 45,
        "start_time": 126980,
        "end_time": 131072,
        "text": "but the warmth of your breath\nwill make odors easier to smell."
    },
    {
        "index": 46,
        "start_time": 131072,
        "end_time": 134022,
        "text": "Second, sniff like you mean it."
    },
    {
        "index": 47,
        "start_time": 134022,
        "end_time": 137322,
        "text": "Smelling actually happens way up near\nthe bridge of our noses"
    },
    {
        "index": 48,
        "start_time": 137322,
        "end_time": 143072,
        "text": "in a postage stamp-sized square\nof tissue called the olfactory epithelium."
    },
    {
        "index": 49,
        "start_time": 143072,
        "end_time": 146801,
        "text": "When we sniff, odor molecules are sucked\nup into our nostrils"
    },
    {
        "index": 50,
        "start_time": 146801,
        "end_time": 148842,
        "text": "until they hit this tissue"
    },
    {
        "index": 51,
        "start_time": 148842,
        "end_time": 153844,
        "text": "where they combine to our olfactory,\nor scent, receptors."
    },
    {
        "index": 52,
        "start_time": 153844,
        "end_time": 157072,
        "text": "When we inhale normally,\nonly a little air makes it there."
    },
    {
        "index": 53,
        "start_time": 157072,
        "end_time": 159543,
        "text": "But one or two solid sharp sniffs"
    },
    {
        "index": 54,
        "start_time": 159543,
        "end_time": 163124,
        "text": "will ensure that more air gets to\nyour smell receptors."
    },
    {
        "index": 55,
        "start_time": 163124,
        "end_time": 164693,
        "text": "After just a few more sniffs,"
    },
    {
        "index": 56,
        "start_time": 164693,
        "end_time": 167872,
        "text": "the receptors, which are best at\nnoticing new smells,"
    },
    {
        "index": 57,
        "start_time": 167872,
        "end_time": 170034,
        "text": "turn off temporarily."
    },
    {
        "index": 58,
        "start_time": 170034,
        "end_time": 173764,
        "text": "So you can give your nose a rest\nand sniff again later."
    },
    {
        "index": 59,
        "start_time": 173764,
        "end_time": 176793,
        "text": "Finally, dwell on the smell."
    },
    {
        "index": 60,
        "start_time": 176793,
        "end_time": 179875,
        "text": "Most smells pass by us \nwith little attention,"
    },
    {
        "index": 61,
        "start_time": 179875,
        "end_time": 181844,
        "text": "but simply noticing what you&#39;re smelling"
    },
    {
        "index": 62,
        "start_time": 181844,
        "end_time": 185245,
        "text": "and by trying to describe it, name it,\nand locate its source,"
    },
    {
        "index": 63,
        "start_time": 185245,
        "end_time": 189393,
        "text": "you can expand your vocabulary of smells."
    },
    {
        "index": 64,
        "start_time": 189393,
        "end_time": 192087,
        "text": "When an odor molecule binds\nto a scent receptor,"
    },
    {
        "index": 65,
        "start_time": 192087,
        "end_time": 195044,
        "text": "it sends an electrical signal\nfrom the sensory neurons"
    },
    {
        "index": 66,
        "start_time": 195044,
        "end_time": 197774,
        "text": "to our brain&#39;s olfactory bulbs."
    },
    {
        "index": 67,
        "start_time": 197774,
        "end_time": 200495,
        "text": "The signal then continues to other\nareas of the brain,"
    },
    {
        "index": 68,
        "start_time": 200495,
        "end_time": 202275,
        "text": "where it&#39;s integrated with taste,"
    },
    {
        "index": 69,
        "start_time": 202275,
        "end_time": 203176,
        "text": "memory,"
    },
    {
        "index": 70,
        "start_time": 203176,
        "end_time": 204530,
        "text": "or emotional information"
    },
    {
        "index": 71,
        "start_time": 204530,
        "end_time": 207855,
        "text": "before registering to us as a smell."
    },
    {
        "index": 72,
        "start_time": 207855,
        "end_time": 212015,
        "text": "FMRI research shows that the extra\ntime spent focusing on scent"
    },
    {
        "index": 73,
        "start_time": 212015,
        "end_time": 215415,
        "text": "changes the brain of experienced smellers."
    },
    {
        "index": 74,
        "start_time": 215415,
        "end_time": 219099,
        "text": "For them, perceiving and imagining odors\nbecomes more automatic"
    },
    {
        "index": 75,
        "start_time": 219099,
        "end_time": 220908,
        "text": "than for non-experts."
    },
    {
        "index": 76,
        "start_time": 220908,
        "end_time": 224249,
        "text": "To get started yourself, take ingredients\nfrom your kitchen:"
    },
    {
        "index": 77,
        "start_time": 224249,
        "end_time": 225198,
        "text": "spices,"
    },
    {
        "index": 78,
        "start_time": 225198,
        "end_time": 225808,
        "text": "vanilla,"
    },
    {
        "index": 79,
        "start_time": 225808,
        "end_time": 226690,
        "text": "or fruit,"
    },
    {
        "index": 80,
        "start_time": 226690,
        "end_time": 228510,
        "text": "but never anything toxic."
    },
    {
        "index": 81,
        "start_time": 228510,
        "end_time": 232250,
        "text": "Close your eyes and have someone\nbring them under your nose."
    },
    {
        "index": 82,
        "start_time": 232250,
        "end_time": 235780,
        "text": "Sniff and try to name the source."
    },
    {
        "index": 83,
        "start_time": 235780,
        "end_time": 239109,
        "text": "Over time, you&#39;ll begin to appreciate\nnuances in familiar odors"
    },
    {
        "index": 84,
        "start_time": 239109,
        "end_time": 243528,
        "text": "and recognize characteristics of new\nand unusual smells."
    },
    {
        "index": 85,
        "start_time": 243528,
        "end_time": 247941,
        "text": "The perfumer has practiced these steps\nenough to become an artist of odor,"
    },
    {
        "index": 86,
        "start_time": 247941,
        "end_time": 250659,
        "text": "but even if you never pursue smelling\nto that degree,"
    },
    {
        "index": 87,
        "start_time": 250659,
        "end_time": 253931,
        "text": "the spectacular result \nof an unspectacular action"
    },
    {
        "index": 88,
        "start_time": 253931,
        "end_time": 257551,
        "text": "will change how you sense \nand experience your days."
    }
]